was involved

21:06.400 --> 21:08.300
and that Howell allowed it
to happen.

21:08.300 --> 21:09.667
But you, Sean...

21:09.667 --> 21:11.133
- Dave was my pal, you know?

21:11.133 --> 21:13.567
Morales fucked up his life
forever.

21:15.900 --> 21:17.533
- Okay.

21:17.533 --> 21:19.233
Thank you.

21:19.233 --> 21:20.667
- That's it, thanks?

21:20.667 --> 21:23.200
- I'll discipline
the three of you,

21:23.200 --> 21:27.000
but how exactly
I don't know yet.

21:27.000 --> 21:28.467
- Right.

21:28.467 --> 21:31.834
- Sean?
- Yeah?

21:31.834 --> 21:34.600
- It takes balls,
what you just did.

21:34.600 --> 21:36.200
- Well, I didn't become
a zoo keeper

21:36.200 --> 21:38.166
just to behave
like one of the animals.

21:44.567 --> 21:46.734
- Put it into your mouth.

21:46.734 --> 21:48.667
- Morales.

21:51.333 --> 21:53.633
I'm releasing you from solitary,
permanently,

21:53.633 --> 21:55.767
putting you back
in Emerald City.

21:55.767 --> 21:56.967
- Why?

21:56.967 --> 21:59.000
- I don't need to give a reason,
do I?

21:59.000 --> 22:00.934
That might make me think twice.

22:00.934 --> 22:03.200
- All right, forget the why.

22:05.166 --> 22:07.367
Hey, Warden,

22:07.367 --> 22:10.934
what do you know
about Nurse Grace?

22:10.934 --> 22:12.467
- Know about her?

22:12.467 --> 22:13.967
Nothing,

22:13.967 --> 22:15.333
except she's worked here
for years.

22:15.333 --> 22:18.700
- If I were you,
I'd check her background.

22:18.700 --> 22:22.834
- What, she's medically
incompetent?

22:22.834 --> 22:24.266
- I'm afraid.

22:24.266 --> 22:26.100
Afraid?

22:26.100 --> 22:27.567
You?

22:27.567 --> 22:28.834
Of her?

22:28.834 --> 22:31.266
- Yeah.

22:31.266 --> 22:33.834
- Must be the medication
you're on.

22:43.867 --> 22:47.367
- Hey, Rebadow.

22:47.367 --> 22:49.967
- What do you want?

22:49.967 --> 22:51.567
- Didn't I give you
all the money

22:51.567 --> 22:54.033
that was left
from that lottery?

22:54.033 --> 22:57.066
- Too late to save my grandson.

22:57.066 --> 22:59.500
- You blame me,
but you shouldn't.

22:59.500 --> 23:02.300
- Who then?
- Morales.

23:02.300 --> 23:05.700
He had Martinez cut me,
which screwed with my head,

23:05.700 --> 23:07.133
which made me take off
with your winnings.

23:07.133 --> 23:10.700
He's the bastard
you should hate.

23:10.700 --> 23:13.934
- There's room in my heart
for both of you.

23:13.934 --> 23:15.600
- Yeah?

23:15.600 --> 23:18.367
Well, Morales is on his way
back to Em City,

23:18.367 --> 23:21.500
and I got fined
and suspended,

23:21.500 --> 23:23.367
a solid month, no pay,
no benefits.

23:23.367 --> 23:25.033
You think I can afford that?

23:25.033 --> 23:28.066
I just got married
for Chrissake.

23:28.066 --> 23:30.300
- I'll repeat my question.

23:30.300 --> 23:34.233
What do you want,
for me to feel sorry for you?

23:34.233 --> 23:36.800
No chance.

23:42.834 --> 23:45.934
- Fuck you, Murphy.

23:55.266 --> 23:58.100
- So, you happy?

23:58.100 --> 24:00.433
Brass gets his ass handed
to him,

24:00.433 --> 24:04.166
we lose a week's vacation,
all for what,

24:04.166 --> 24:06.700
Enrique fucking Morales?

24:06.700 --> 24:08.900
- For the truth, Howell,
for justice.

24:08.900 --> 24:10.300
- Justice.

24:10.300 --> 24:14.300
Justice, my pink ass.

24:14.300 --> 24:16.133
Oh, call the blood banks.

24:16.133 --> 24:18.834
Here comes another
bleeding heart.

24:24.900 --> 24:27.433
- So, Leo told me
all the gory details.

24:27.433 --> 24:29.533
- I'm sorry, Tim.
- You're sorry?

24:29.533 --> 24:32.033
I bring you into Oz
because we've known each other

24:32.033 --> 24:35.633
since sixth grade,
because you're the one person

24:35.633 --> 24:39.767
in my entire life
that I can trust

24:39.767 --> 24:42.767
with my life, if necessary.

24:42.767 --> 24:46.166
But then, see,
I find out I can't trust you,

24:46.166 --> 24:48.166
that you're just another
thickheaded,

24:48.166 --> 24:51.734
redneck slug who uses his badge
as a weapon.

24:51.734 --> 24:53.166
- You're right,
you're absolutely right.

24:53.166 --> 24:55.200
- Don't you fuckin'
agree with me!

24:55.200 --> 24:57.734
I'm telling you to fuck off!

25:00.433 --> 25:03.834
- Listen, I've betrayed
your trust.

25:03.834 --> 25:05.734
If you don't see me
getting it back,

25:05.734 --> 25:07.767
maybe I should just transfer out
of Em City.

25:07.767 --> 25:08.900
- What?

25:08.900 --> 25:10.533
- Maybe I should
just quit altogether.

25:10.533 --> 25:12.233
- No. Jesus!

25:12.233 --> 25:14.934
Jesus, stop being
so fuckin' remorseful!

25:14.934 --> 25:16.266
- What, you don't want me
to be remorseful?

25:16.266 --> 25:18.266
- No, yes!

25:28.533 --> 25:29.934
We're going to dinner tonight.

25:29.934 --> 25:31.800
You're paying.

25:33.567 --> 25:35.266
- Okay.

25:37.367 --> 25:43.033
- Sean, I'm proud of you
that you stepped forward.

25:43.033 --> 25:46.633
It means I can
still trust you.

25:55.066 --> 25:57.867
- Morales?

25:57.867 --> 26:01.333
Morales...

26:01.333 --> 26:04.266
I'm sorry to disturb you.

26:04.266 --> 26:07.433
That sedative I gave you
was pretty strong, huh?

26:07.433 --> 26:09.200
- Yeah.

26:09.200 --> 26:11.333
- It's a precaution.

26:11.333 --> 26:13.633
You're a big fella.

26:13.633 --> 26:14.934
I didn't want to struggle.

26:14.934 --> 26:16.734
- Struggle?

26:16.734 --> 26:18.500
- Martinez was so weak,

26:18.500 --> 26:22.867
he couldn't fight me,
but you...

26:22.867 --> 26:24.834
Say your prayers, Enrique.

26:24.834 --> 26:26.200
- No, don't.

26:26.200 --> 26:27.667
- You're just like Martinez,

26:27.667 --> 26:30.300
a nasty man
who deserves to die.

26:40.133 --> 26:41.367
- Knock, knock.

26:41.367 --> 26:42.767
- Hi.

26:42.767 --> 26:45.066
Can you say, "Who's there?"

26:45.066 --> 26:48.433
- Might be a while before
she can say Agamemnon Busmalis.

26:48.433 --> 26:52.133
Oh, God, she's gorgeous.

26:54.934 --> 26:56.700
Hi.

26:56.700 --> 26:58.266
Thank you.

26:58.266 --> 27:01.633
Oh, that fresh smell
of baby skin,

27:01.633 --> 27:03.367
in Oz of all places.

27:03.367 --> 27:05.467
Can I touch her?

27:05.467 --> 27:07.700
- Of course.

27:13.300 --> 27:14.600
- Can I keep her?

27:14.600 --> 27:17.266
- How about we share?

27:17.266 --> 27:20.166
Ruby needs a father, Agamemnon,

27:20.166 --> 27:22.400
and I need you back.

27:24.533 --> 27:28.133
Agamemnon, will you marry me?

27:28.133 --> 27:30.300
- What?

27:30.300 --> 27:33.400
You're proposing to me now?

27:33.400 --> 27:35.734
- Is that a yes?

27:35.734 --> 27:38.934
- I think so.

27:38.934 --> 27:40.800
Yeah.

27:40.800 --> 27:44.133
Oh, my God, yes!
- Yes.

27:46.266 --> 27:47.834
Oh...

27:47.834 --> 27:49.734
- Oh, you little doll.
- Yes.

27:49.734 --> 27:52.266
Little doll.

27:52.266 --> 27:55.033
- I can't work
in the library anymore.

27:55.033 --> 27:56.133
- What?

27:56.133 --> 27:57.467
Why not?

27:57.467 --> 27:59.500
- I'd rather not get
into the specifics.

27:59.500 --> 28:02.500
- Given that I run this place,
I need specifics.

28:02.500 --> 28:04.033
Something happen
I should know about?

28:04.033 --> 28:05.166
- No.

28:05.166 --> 28:07.100
- Trouble with other inmates?

28:07.100 --> 28:10.200
- No.
- Is it Stella?

28:13.700 --> 28:15.633
Are you two having problems?

28:15.633 --> 28:16.734
- No.

28:16.734 --> 28:17.867
- Well, what is it then?

28:17.867 --> 28:20.033
Did you forget
the fuckin' alphabet?

28:30.133 --> 28:32.033
- I don't want
to get Robert in trouble,

28:32.033 --> 28:34.166
but I thought you should know.

28:34.166 --> 28:36.800
- It's not like Rebadow
to just stop showing up,

28:36.800 --> 28:40.800
though he did come to me asking
to be switched to another job.

28:40.800 --> 28:44.767
You have any idea why?

28:44.767 --> 28:47.233
- No.

28:47.233 --> 28:50.133
- He's probably still depressed
about Alex Jr.

28:50.133 --> 28:52.000
- Who?

28:52.000 --> 28:54.166
- His grandson.

28:54.166 --> 28:57.100
He died last year of leukemia.

28:57.100 --> 28:58.800
- His grandson?

28:58.800 --> 29:00.734
Of leukemia?

29:00.734 --> 29:04.333
- I didn't say anything
when I initially came to you.

29:04.333 --> 29:06.467
I thought that the library
would be a good place

29:06.467 --> 29:09.133
to distract his mind
from his misery.

29:09.133 --> 29:11.266
Anyway, he'll be there tomorrow.

29:13.266 --> 29:15.600
- So, I did good by you
with "ball four"?

29:15.600 --> 29:17.066
I hit a home run.

29:17.066 --> 29:19.533
- I like the beaver shooting,
where the players

29:19.533 --> 29:21.367
drilled the holes
in the door of the hotel room

29:21.367 --> 29:23.033
and watched
the stewardess fuckin'?

29:23.033 --> 29:25.033
- Yeah, well,
it's fun for the guys,

29:25.033 --> 29:27.867
but how would you like
to have been on the other side?

29:27.867 --> 29:30.700
What they did
was an invasion of privacy.

29:30.700 --> 29:33.266
- Oh, whatever.
- Whatever.

29:33.266 --> 29:37.533
Now, this is a very good book
about women.

29:37.533 --> 29:39.967
And I thought something
wilderness-based,

29:39.967 --> 29:43.233
"Into Thin Air," might be
a nice antidote to Oz.

29:43.233 --> 29:45.467
- Do I look like
a fuckin' Boy Scout?

29:45.467 --> 29:46.800
- Scout, no.

29:46.800 --> 29:49.934
Boy, yes.

29:49.934 --> 29:52.233
I'll just be a minute.

29:54.900 --> 29:57.433
Robert, I'd like to talk to you.

30:01.266 --> 30:03.600
When I told you
about my breast cancer,

30:03.600 --> 30:07.467
I wasn't asking you to watch me
waste away and die, Robert.

30:07.467 --> 30:11.734
I don't need you for that,
if that's what you're afraid of.

30:17.433 --> 30:19.533
I know about Alex Jr.

30:22.000 --> 30:25.200
This isn't that.

30:25.200 --> 30:28.233
I know you're thinking you can't
go through the grief again,

30:28.233 --> 30:30.900
but what if you're missing
the chance

30:30.900 --> 30:34.266
to go through the joy,
the joy of being there

30:34.266 --> 30:36.633
for someone who is
going to make it?

30:39.000 --> 30:41.166
According to Blake,
they go hand in hand,

30:41.166 --> 30:45.233
joy and grief, "piping down
the valleys wild," remember?

30:51.200 --> 30:53.667
Stop being an asshole.

30:57.166 --> 30:58.533
- If she's talking to you,
old man,

30:58.533 --> 31:00.433
show some respect
and talk back.

31:00.433 --> 31:01.700
- That's enough, Pablo.

31:01.700 --> 31:03.667
Take your book,
we're done for today.

31:39.400 --> 31:42.000
- 70 times 77.

31:42.000 --> 31:43.900
Jesus said
that's how many times

31:43.900 --> 31:46.100
you're supposed to forgive
your brother.

31:46.100 --> 31:49.133
- Hank and I are still working
on seven.

31:49.133 --> 31:51.867
Meanwhile, an innocent man
nailed to a cross

31:51.867 --> 31:54.467
with iron spikes
says while dying,

31:54.467 --> 31:56.734
"Forgive them, Father.

31:56.734 --> 31:59.266
They know not what they do."

31:59.266 --> 32:02.967
Kind of raises the stakes
for the rest of us, huh?

32:07.533 --> 32:09.967
- Officer Schwartzmyer says
on the night of the murder,

32:09.967 --> 32:11.266
you started screaming.

32:11.266 --> 32:13.333
- I had a bad reaction
to the medicine.

32:13.333 --> 32:14.934
- As he came over
to check you out,

32:14.934 --> 32:18.033
someone snuck in the private
room and stabbed Mayor Loewen.

32:18.033 --> 32:19.767
- The medicine
was giving me hives.

32:19.767 --> 32:22.400
- Mr. Kelsch,
Dr. Nathan tells us

32:22.400 --> 32:24.967
you weren't having a negative
reaction to the medicine.

32:24.967 --> 32:26.867
- I couldn't stop itching.

32:26.867 --> 32:28.700
- You want to know what I think?

32:28.700 --> 32:30.300
I think you were paid to
distract

32:30.300 --> 32:32.567
Officer Schwartzmyer
from his post.

32:32.567 --> 32:35.000
- The scratching
was driving me crazy.

32:35.000 --> 32:37.000
- That makes you
guilty of murder.

32:37.000 --> 32:39.300
That means you go
to death row.

32:39.300 --> 32:40.300
- Huh?

32:40.300 --> 32:41.900
Death row?

32:41.900 --> 32:43.467
For hives?

32:55.500 --> 32:57.000
- Okay, Brandt, here's the deal.

32:57.000 --> 32:59.367
We now know you're guilty
of killing Wilson Loewen.

32:59.367 --> 33:00.934
- That's a lie.

33:00.934 --> 33:03.066
- We have statements
from two of the other inmates

33:03.066 --> 33:04.734
who were in the ward that night.

33:04.734 --> 33:06.800
They say they saw you
get out of bed

33:06.800 --> 33:07.800
and go into Loewen's room.

33:07.800 --> 33:09.200
- They're lying.

33:09.200 --> 33:11.834
- We also have a confession
from Lionel Kelsch

33:11.834 --> 33:15.166
who says you offered him $1,000
to distract the officer on duty.

33:15.166 --> 33:16.834
- He's a liar.

33:16.834 --> 33:18.500
- Okay, we'll play it your way.

33:18.500 --> 33:20.667
You have the right
to remain silent.

33:20.667 --> 33:22.800
- Aryans are gonna be so pissed
when they hear you're guilty

33:22.800 --> 33:24.500
of killing their hero.
- Anything you say

33:24.500 --> 33:26.166
may be used
against you in a court of law.

33:26.166 --> 33:29.100
- Without my protection,
you'll be dead within the hour.

33:29.100 --> 33:32.133
- You have the right to a lawyer
before speaking to me.

33:32.133 --> 33:35.400
- All right.
All right, all right.

33:35.400 --> 33:37.633
I'll tell you who hired me.

33:37.633 --> 33:41.333
It was that CO,
what's his name?

33:41.333 --> 33:42.734
Johnson.

33:51.800 --> 33:55.200
- Johnson, how's it going?

33:55.200 --> 33:56.934
- Not bad, sir, and you?

33:56.934 --> 33:59.033
- The usual brouhaha.

33:59.033 --> 34:03.767
Hey, I hear you just
bought a car, Jaguar.

34:03.767 --> 34:05.066
- Yup.

34:05.066 --> 34:06.767
- That's a beautiful automobile.

34:06.767 --> 34:08.934
Pretty pricey on a CO's salary.

34:08.934 --> 34:11.667
- My wife's maiden aunt kicked.

34:11.667 --> 34:13.433
She left us a little dough.

34:13.433 --> 34:15.633
- Nice.

34:15.633 --> 34:18.233
Willy Brandt.

34:18.233 --> 34:19.734
- What, sir?

34:19.734 --> 34:23.033
- Willy Brandt confessed
to the murder of Wilson Loewen.

34:23.033 --> 34:25.500
- Congratulations.

34:25.500 --> 34:28.100
How did you manage
to get that thing to spill?

34:28.100 --> 34:30.333
- The truth?

34:32.333 --> 34:33.967
We lied.

34:33.967 --> 34:36.000
We told Brandt
that we had two witnesses,

34:36.000 --> 34:38.633
which we don't,
and that his partner confessed,

34:38.633 --> 34:40.400
which he didn't.

34:40.400 --> 34:41.934
- Brilliant.

34:41.934 --> 34:43.633
- Oh, here's the good part.

34:43.633 --> 34:46.333
Brandt claims that you offered
to pay him $5,000

34:46.333 --> 34:49.667
to waste Wilson Loewen.

34:49.667 --> 34:52.233
Not that I believe him
or anything.

34:52.233 --> 34:53.800
- No, sir.

34:53.800 --> 34:55.834
He's a lying piece of shit.

34:55.834 --> 34:57.533
- Right.

34:57.533 --> 35:00.333
Well, good night.

35:03.500 --> 35:05.533
Enjoy that car.

35:18.266 --> 35:20.567
- Hey, it's me.
We got a problem.

35:20.567 --> 35:22.367
Glynn knows I set up the murder.

35:22.367 --> 35:24.300
What do you want me to do?

35:26.767 --> 35:28.367
Okay.

35:32.600 --> 35:35.800
- He brought the devil in here,
your son.

35:35.800 --> 35:37.433
Do you hear me?

35:37.433 --> 35:41.133
Your baby boy
got butt-fucked by Satan,

35:41.133 --> 35:43.967
and now we're all gonna burn,

35:43.967 --> 35:46.500
you fuckin' bitch!

35:49.533 --> 35:51.467
- I'm an idiot.

35:51.467 --> 35:53.734
I thought by talking to the man
who killed Timmy,

35:53.734 --> 35:56.600
I would get to know more
about my boy,

35:56.600 --> 35:59.667
that I would understand how
he became the man he became.

35:59.667 --> 36:01.867
- Well, like I said,

36:01.867 --> 36:04.100
Jazz Hoyt isn't very coherent
these days.

36:04.100 --> 36:06.834
He's been ruled mentally insane
by the court of appeals.

36:06.834 --> 36:09.200
Tomorrow they're moving him up
to the psych unit.

36:09.200 --> 36:10.333
- So, what do I do now?

36:10.333 --> 36:12.734
How do I calm this guilt
inside of me?

36:12.734 --> 36:14.500
And don't tell me to pray.

36:14.500 --> 36:17.900
I've prayed so hard
my knees hurt.

36:17.900 --> 36:20.934
- Well, when praying stalls,
I usually try to imagine

36:20.934 --> 36:23.533
what my dad would've done
in the situation.

36:23.533 --> 36:27.266
That's an excellent idea.

36:27.266 --> 36:29.934
Do you drink, Father?

36:29.934 --> 36:31.300
- Ah, sure.

36:31.300 --> 36:32.633
- Good.

36:32.633 --> 36:34.800
I'll go into town,
I'll get us a quart of Jameson's

36:34.800 --> 36:36.567
and sit in the dark
and drink until dawn,

36:36.567 --> 36:38.667
'cause that's how my dad would
have handled the situation.

36:38.667 --> 36:40.500
- Mrs. Kirk, I-I...

36:40.500 --> 36:43.367
- I'm joking, Father.

36:43.367 --> 36:46.266
Call me Jessica.

36:46.266 --> 36:47.934
- Call me Ray.

36:47.934 --> 36:50.467
- Ray...

36:50.467 --> 36:52.900
Like a ray of sunshine.

36:58.567 --> 37:02.166
I think what I should do
is what I should've done

37:02.166 --> 37:05.100
when Timmy was alive,
and that's volunteer

37:05.100 --> 37:07.700
to work at Oswald,

37:07.700 --> 37:10.934
help men like my son
become better people.

37:10.934 --> 37:12.934
- Volunteer?

37:12.934 --> 37:14.233
What would you do?

37:14.233 --> 37:15.834
- I'm a nurse.

37:15.834 --> 37:17.433
I bet they could use some help
in the hospital ward.

37:17.433 --> 37:19.066
- Yes.

37:19.066 --> 37:20.900
- You'll set that up for me,
Ray?

37:20.900 --> 37:22.367
- Of course.

37:22.367 --> 37:23.934
- Thank you.

37:26.934 --> 37:30.133
I consider you
my really good friend.

37:41.567 --> 37:43.633
- Morning, kiddies.

37:43.633 --> 37:46.333
- Do I have to go get more ECT?

37:46.333 --> 37:48.033
- Later.

37:48.033 --> 37:51.166
Come on, Hoyt,
time to move you up to psych.

37:55.567 --> 37:57.133
Hoyt!

38:00.834 --> 38:03.033
- What the fuck?

38:03.033 --> 38:04.967
I'm bleeding.

38:07.367 --> 38:08.500
- He'll sleep.

38:08.500 --> 38:11.600
I sedated him.

38:11.600 --> 38:13.700
- He's got no cuts
on his forehead.

38:13.700 --> 38:15.200
What's causing the bleeding?

38:15.200 --> 38:19.834
- A rare condition
called hematidrosis.

38:19.834 --> 38:21.233
Underneath the skin
there are these

38:21.233 --> 38:23.700
tiny blood vessels,
capillaries.

38:23.700 --> 38:26.567
When people are stressed,
they sweat, right?

38:26.567 --> 38:29.633
Well, sometimes
under extreme stress

38:29.633 --> 38:31.567
the capillaries hemorrhage,

38:31.567 --> 38:34.734
