the children of our community

45:04.300 --> 45:07.000
with lethal drugs
while I have fought

45:07.000 --> 45:09.000
to keep those
same children safe.

45:09.000 --> 45:12.100
And now, just because
we both find ourselves

45:12.100 --> 45:15.400
in this clap shack, you want
to believe that we have a bond.

45:15.400 --> 45:18.266
We don't.
- We do!

45:18.266 --> 45:22.033
I've seen the error of my ways,
and I'm trying to correct them.

45:22.033 --> 45:25.066
- I don't believe you.

45:28.400 --> 45:30.834
- You know, Burr,
that Neema,

45:30.834 --> 45:33.066
he's a pompous
piece of shit, man.

45:33.066 --> 45:36.433
I say it's time he learned
who's the boss around here.

45:36.433 --> 45:38.233
- You want him dead, O'Reily?

45:38.233 --> 45:41.333
- I wouldn't weep if he was.

45:41.333 --> 45:44.967
- If you really  want
to do Neema some harm,

45:44.967 --> 45:47.834
tie him to your mother's crime.

45:47.834 --> 45:50.266
- What do you mean?

45:50.266 --> 45:51.700
- You're a clever boy.

45:51.700 --> 45:53.767
You figure that one out.

45:58.367 --> 46:01.166
- Who's the hardest person
of all to forgive?

46:01.166 --> 46:02.700
Oneself.

46:02.700 --> 46:05.400
The demons inside,
they laugh at the thought.

46:05.400 --> 46:07.500
- When you forgive
some other guy,

46:07.500 --> 46:09.266
he's not likely to turn you
down, say, "Fuck that."

46:09.266 --> 46:11.700
- Tryin' to forgive yourself,
though,

46:11.700 --> 46:13.233
it's "Fuck that" all the time.

46:13.233 --> 46:16.233
- Ten years go by, you still
can't let yourself off the hook.

46:16.233 --> 46:18.667
- 15 years, 20, 40.

46:18.667 --> 46:20.934
You gonna take that grudge
against yourself to the grave?

46:20.934 --> 46:23.166
- You gonna carry it for
eternity?

46:30.266 --> 46:32.000
- Well, well, well.
Agent Taylor.

46:32.000 --> 46:33.033
Are you here to visit me?

46:33.033 --> 46:35.200
- Fuck you, Keller.

46:35.200 --> 46:39.033
- Aww, G-man,
don't get grumpy.

46:39.033 --> 46:41.233
You're the one who made
the deal with Heekin.

46:41.233 --> 46:42.600
You're the one
who got him to fib.

46:42.600 --> 46:45.033
- He saw you dump the body.

46:45.033 --> 46:46.867
- Hey, wasn't it
J. Edgar Hoover who said,

46:46.867 --> 46:48.200
"Cheaters never prosper"?

46:50.000 --> 46:52.133
- Careful there, sir.

46:52.133 --> 46:54.533
- You killed two other men,
Keller,

46:54.533 --> 46:57.400
and I'm gonna get you
for one of them.

47:09.767 --> 47:12.200
- Henry Stanton?
I'm Tobias Beecher.

47:12.200 --> 47:14.867
Sister Peter Marie
suggested I come see you.

47:14.867 --> 47:17.367
- You're the one doing
pro bono work, right?

47:17.367 --> 47:18.867
- Yeah, that's right.

47:18.867 --> 47:20.934
- Helping the prisoners
with legal shit and such.

47:20.934 --> 47:22.767
Well, I hurt my back
doing sanitation duty

47:22.767 --> 47:24.400
a few months ago.

47:24.400 --> 47:27.500
Dr. Nathan told me not to do
anything too strenuous.

47:27.500 --> 47:30.033
I told my COs and they put me
right back to work again

47:30.033 --> 47:33.300
because they think I'm faking,
but I'm not.

47:33.300 --> 47:36.166
In fact,
they give me harder work.

47:36.166 --> 47:39.767
I complain to my unit manager,
nothing changes.

47:39.767 --> 47:42.233
And the other day
I screwed up my back again.

47:42.233 --> 47:46.400
- Uh...
Well, off the top of my head,

47:46.400 --> 47:49.033
it appears the COs
violated your rights

47:49.033 --> 47:51.734
under the eighth amendment,
deliberate indifference.

47:51.734 --> 47:54.767
Let me talk to Dr. Nathan,
the officers involved,

47:54.767 --> 47:57.500
and Warden Glynn,
let me see what I can do.

47:57.500 --> 47:59.533
Meanwhile, take it easy.

47:59.533 --> 48:00.900
Back injuries suck.

48:00.900 --> 48:02.500
- Thanks a lot, man.

48:02.500 --> 48:04.433
- Stanton is not lying, Leo.

48:04.433 --> 48:06.333
I gave him the proper
medical documentation

48:06.333 --> 48:07.767
at least three times.

48:07.767 --> 48:09.834
- Okay, the COs screwed up.

48:09.834 --> 48:11.266
They will be reprimanded.

48:11.266 --> 48:13.133
- That's not good enough.

48:13.133 --> 48:15.066
I've got a rock-solid case here,
Warden.

48:15.066 --> 48:16.834
If we go to court, I'll win.

48:16.834 --> 48:18.700
- What do you want?

48:18.700 --> 48:21.767
- Full physical rehab for
Stanton at the prison's expense

48:21.767 --> 48:25.166
and a guarantee that he'll
be assigned light duty tasks.

48:27.100 --> 48:28.600
- Okay.

48:28.600 --> 48:30.233
- And I want those
two Cos fired.

48:30.233 --> 48:32.633
- Beecher--
- Gone, today.

48:32.633 --> 48:34.166
- The union will fight this.

48:34.166 --> 48:37.633
- So, let the union
take the heat.

48:37.633 --> 48:39.900
- All right, they're fired,
I'm busy.

48:42.734 --> 48:44.233
- You're good at this, Tobias.

48:44.233 --> 48:46.333
- You ain't seen nothing yet.

48:51.200 --> 48:54.200
- So, how are you adjusting
to life after death row?

48:54.200 --> 48:55.934
- I'm bored.

48:55.934 --> 48:58.133
